>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1>    I first want to say thanks to Lagdalen and Flarren for their leadership.  I thouhgt it went well considering it was our first time and we were low on people.  Also thank you vaard and Ogun for rezing me six times.<br>
   I dont think there is anything new I can add other than there were a few people who were spamming way to much.  During a raid, either talk in &quot;tells&quot; or dont talk at all.  There is plenty of time later to chat.  Also, some commands like, ready, set, GO GO GO would have been great for our first wave.  I saw people going in helter skelter in stead of a massive wave.<br>
   In case others dont know, during the battle I was to transfer my mana to my group healer.  So to those of you telling me to get in there and nuke, I was already doing my job. Unfortunately, I dont have any relevant nukes that are not fire based.  So I was relegated to pumping mana for heals and rezzes.<br>
   Even though we lost, I really enjoyed being a part of that.  I am certain that we will have a much better outcome next time.  I hope we are back on the waiting list.  <br>
As a fellow Reptile, I have to say I am very ashamed of Lord Nagefen.  I hope you all will not judge the rest of we reptiles by his example.<br>
<br>
Jabberwauk <br>
Rainmakers of Karana (officer)<br>
