Anyways, thats enough of my comments, oh well, we gave it a good try, sorry I couldn't be there for a second attempt.<br>
Euwyn Elementaltamer<br>
Magician of the 51st Voceration<br>
<br>
<br>
P.S. I liked the strategy of splitting the tanks, and I think that it may be useful to instead of waiting 15 seconds to send pets in like we did, let them go in right away...Heres why: To start off every fight, Naggy and Vox both cast their fear at the first agro, fearing generally about 1/2 the tanks, and mage pets always. So I think we should just let them be and go after him once their fear wears(generally 8-10seconds). They generally do another fear every 20-30 seconds, and so by the time they actually get to naggy if we put em in at 15 seconds, they will be useless, but if they actualy start tanking at 15 seconds(by the time they get back to him after being feared), they'll have more time on him. Also, for the 45% caster nuke point, just a recommendation, but I think it should really go back to about 70%. The reason we failed is because there were no tanks left to keep it off the casters, well, tanks can't last that long, and have one life, so if casters go in earlier , we can take him down to 0% hp faster than if they wait, and if its faster, more likely we are to have tanks still alive, rather then all dead and faileing at 8% hp<br>
